programme.desc: Everyone from the chief to the trainees at the Clementon Fire Department is convinced that the ghost of a former member is haunting their firehouse.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lady Vampire
programme.desc: PRS investigates a case involving single mom, Dawn, and her 5-year-old daughter, both of whom are tormented by the appearance of a hag they call "lady vampire."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Man of the House
programme.desc: PRS is called to help a grandmother and her frightened grandson when renovations on her 19th century house stir up the pipe-smoking specter of a former tenant named Alfred.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Basement
programme.desc: A history of violence may connect the spiritual activity in Heidi's Ohio home to a long run of misery and cruelty.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Spirits of the Slave Dungeon
programme.desc: Ryan books a two-night case in a real haunted jail in Charleston, SC, but PRS soon realizes the spirits themselves are being held there against their will and subjected to an unjust form of torture.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Permission To Do Harm
programme.desc: When a mirror levitates and shatters on its own, P.R.S. heeds the call to investigate a spirit that has been unleashed on an unsuspecting family. Ryan must track down the spirit and contain it before it does irreparable damage.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghost On the Tracks
programme.desc: PRS is called to a New Jersey beauty salon, but they soon learn that the building's proximity to deadly train tracks might be the true cause of spirit activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder
programme.desc: A large family in Shrewsbury, MA, has been living with a spirit for the last 40 years. To most of the siblings, the entity is menacing and evil, but Sandy seems to have a different connection.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Alton Towers
programme.desc: The team visits Alton Towers and has a frightening brush with something more terrifying than the usual thrills and spills of the funfair.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Dartford Library
programme.desc: Dartford Library comes under Yvette and the crew's scrutiny as they experience strange poltergeist activity involving books, and contact the denizens that appear to cling to the building.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Stockport Workhouse
programme.desc: The Stockport Workhouse opened on a bleak Christmas Day in 1841 and quickly filled with the desperate and jobless. The Dickensian atmosphere gives Yvette and the team a night to remember!

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park, Old Hall
programme.desc: Journalist Carol Thatcher joins the team as they journey to Tatton Old Hall. They investigate reports of a misogynistic presence as well as a mischievous spirit who plays tricks on the unwary.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Cammell Laird
programme.desc: Untimely death, fear and vast emptiness await the team in Merseyside. They investigate the offices and huge construction hall of what was once the heart of the Cammell Laird shipyard.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sutton House
programme.desc: Musician and amateur ghost hunter Lee Ryan joins Yvette as the team encounter poltergeists, fear and phantoms at Sutton House. They find a veritable treasure trove of reported paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park Mansion
programme.desc: The crew investigates Tatton Park Mansion. There is so much reported paranormal activity within its walls that certain phantoms must walk the grounds because there is no room for them inside.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Matlock Bath Pavilion
programme.desc: The team travels to the spa town of Matlock Bath to investigate strange phenomena in the pavilion. Once a tourist destination, it is now home to a mining museum, a night club and ghostly apparitions.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Plane Death
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark investigate a gang of drug smugglers after an old friend of Mark's has mysteriously disappeared.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: One Winged Angels
programme.desc: Jonathan attempts to fan the flames of love between a woman and her ex-husband's best friend. But his efforts backfire when he falls for the woman himself.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Going Home, Going Home
programme.desc: Mark is in a state between life and death when he's critically injured in a car accident. Jonathan takes Mark back to childhood to give him a second chance to tell his grandfather how much he loves him.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: As Difficult as ABC
programme.desc: Jonathan steps in when a heart condition sidelines a promising basketball player's dreams.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Child of God
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are on hand when a dying woman attempts a reconciliation with her estranged father. She is a single mother who wants her family to take the child.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Match Made in Heaven
programme.desc: Scotty is a lovelorn quadriplegic with a successful law practice. Jonathan is happy to play cupid, but Mark isn't so thrilled about it, because the woman in question is his cousin.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Banker and The Bum
programme.desc: A greedy banker and a good-hearted bum switch places. The bum dies, but the banker is now infused with love and generosity.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Brightest Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark meet a child star whose fame is spoiling her rotten, destroying her family and taking away her childhood.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Picture Perfect
programme.desc: Stacey is a homemaker who aspires to a career in photography but is embarrassed to show her own face. After a makeover in the glam capitol, Beverly Hills, will Stacey be picture perfect?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Carolyne Robinson
programme.desc: Mother of four Carolyne Robinson has found domestic bliss to be something of an oxymoron. Fiona McDonald and her team of experts are charged with turning Caroline into a fashionable mum and they have just 10 days to do it.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Kicking Out The Old Look
programme.desc: Janet, a hard-bodied kick boxer, is on round two of her life. A bad marriage had her on the ropes, but she has come back strong and is a college freshman with a new fiancé and wants a face to match her young heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Liz O'Reilly
programme.desc: Bedford deputy newspaper editor, Liz O'Reilly, 40, has some stories to tell and a lifetime of sun, stress and smoking means they're mostly written on her face. Presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand to crack the whip.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Dolled Up
programme.desc: Sara is a lady with a rough medical history who is still able to maintain a heart of gold. After helping her ailing grandmother for many years and conquering a litany of illness herself, Sara and the Glam Squad are ready to update her look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Taryn Couper
programme.desc: Taryn Couper admits she's stuck in the 1970s so it's up to Fiona McDonald and her team of experts to turn her from Hamilton hippie to boho chic, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Lorraine Harvey
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team take on the challenge of Lorraine Harvey from Tunbridge Wells.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Under New Management
programme.desc: Victoria is a mom and apartment manager without any personal time. Her job creates a lack of structure for her to spend with her family. The Ten Years Younger team will brighten her smile, revive her appearance and open her eyes to new possibilities.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Nicki Hall
programme.desc: Nicki Hall wears her hardships on her face and she's aging quickly. But trying to dress sporty like her teenage daughters just makes her look older. This week Fiona McDonald and a team of experts help turn Nicky into the young woman she is at heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Unstick The 80s
programme.desc: Between her career as an attorney and raising two children, Cindi hasn't found time to update her look since the 80s. She hasn't bought an outfit since her first child was born, six years ago. The 10 Years Younger crew is ready to unleash the team.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: You Can't Outrun The Sun
programme.desc: Diana is a substitute teacher, but in her youth she was a sun-worshipper and a party girl. Those two things combined have resulted in severly damaged skin. Experts help Diana go from mousy teacher to red-hot mama, but will she look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Deconstructing Mike
programme.desc: Mike has spent a lifetime in the blazing sun and it has taken its toll. He is tired of being referred to as the "old guy" and would like to look younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Estelle Bell
programme.desc: Estelle Bell is desperately in need of a confidence shake up. Can Fiona McDonald and her team of experts convince Estelle she's still young at heart and make her look 10 Years Younger in just 10 days?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 15

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 16

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 17

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 18
programme.desc: Mark makes pizza for a teenage sleepover, whilst Martin tumble-dries son FK's bibs – which disastrous results.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 19

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 20

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Germany´s Supercar Rally

programme.title: On Tour: Night of the Jumps

programme.title: On Tour: Bus Stunts with Action Concept

programme.title: On Tour: ADAC Bavaria Historic Rallye

programme.title: On Tour: Truck Grand Prix am Nuerburgring

programme.title: On Tour: Fun at the BMW Enduro Park

programme.sub-title: Fun at the BMW Enduro Park

programme.title: On Tour: 125 Years Mercedes

programme.title: On Tour: BMW M1 Meeting

programme.title: On Tour: Stockcar Race

programme.title: On Tour: Air Show

programme.desc: Laura has felt oppressed by a violent spirit ever since she heard a chilling EVP in the fall of 2007. The 26-year-old claims she's been beaten, choked, even forcibly submerged.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Matlock Bath Pavilion
programme.desc: The team travels to the spa town of Matlock Bath to investigate strange phenomena in the pavilion. Once a tourist destination, it is now home to a mining museum, a night club and ghostly apparitions.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hever Castle
programme.desc: The majestic location of Hever Castle in Kent is inextricably linked to the doomed relationship between King Henry VIII and Anne Boleyn. What regal phantoms will the investigation reveal?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Rasnov Citadel Night - Part One
programme.desc: Traveling deep into the heart of Romania to the Transylvanian mountains, the team experiences its most frightening investigation yet as it uncovers skeletons and ghosts perhaps best left alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Rasnov Citadel Night - Part Two
programme.desc: Yvette gets the fright of her life during her second night in Rasnov Citadel. She takes the plunge and drops 210 feet to the bottom of a disused well that hides sinister evidence of an untimely death.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kasteel Doorwerth, Arnhem, Netherlands
programme.desc: On their first investigation in the Netherlands, the team encounter spirits who were tortured or have committed suicide. Which shocked member of the team will they inhabit to express their suffering?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Morecambe Winter Gardens - Part One
programme.desc: Spirits, mysterious death and a structure with a split personality await the team and guest medium Brian Shepherd as they investigate ghostly activity at the Winter Gardens.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Morecambe Winter Gardens - Part Two
programme.desc: The team spends a second night at Morcambe Winter Gardens. After a night spent investigating the "good side," the team faces the terrors of the "evil side" of the gardens' split personality.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Oxford Castle Unlocked
programme.desc: The team investigate Oxford Castle Unlocked, a tourist attraction based on the site of a former prison complex. With such a brutal history, it is said to be rife with paranormal activity.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Brightest Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark meet a child star whose fame is spoiling her rotten, destroying her family and taking away her childhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Investment In Caring
programme.desc: Jonathan encourages residents in a neighborhood to unite against a cold-hearted developer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Right Thing
programme.desc: Jonathan inspires a young man to help the grandfather who has recently been placed in a nursing home.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 1
programme.desc: Lizzy MacGill is a horse trainer's young daughter who elopes with Garth Armstrong, a privileged man.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help Lizzie. The new bride has cancer and she is pregnant.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 1
programme.desc: Mark and Jonathan become counselors at a camp for children with cancer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are helping patients at Camp Good Times in different ways. But a father still refuses to deal with his son's illness.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Estelle Bell
programme.desc: Estelle Bell is desperately in need of a confidence shake up. Can Fiona McDonald and her team of experts convince Estelle she's still young at heart and make her look 10 Years Younger in just 10 days?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Diana Turner
programme.desc: Working with men all day, Diana Turner feels more like one of the lads than one of the ladies. It's up to Fiona McDonald and the team of experts to banish Diana's tom-boy look and make her appear 10 Years Younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hip Hop Momma
programme.desc: Jessika is a working mother of two young children who's responsibilities of motherhood has left her with little time and energy for her appearance. Now she wishes she could regain some of that old sexy feeling while being a mom.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Scrubs No More
programme.desc: Darcey spends her days caring for three kids and her nights working as a nurse, with no time left for herself. Experts perform the latest procedures in dermatology and dentistry, and the glam squad takes her from scrubs to sass.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Changing For The Better
programme.desc: After Lasik to get rid of her glasses and some dermatology to give her skin a more youthful appearance, Laura gets overhauled by the Glam Squad. Now, Laura can see without her coke bottle glasses, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear
programme.desc: Crystal has been taking care of other people since she was eight years old; after her mother had a stroke, she cared for her younger brother. Crystal needs to focus on herself for a change. Experts do what it takes to reclaim her youthful appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Teacher Learns A Lesson
programme.desc: After a major dental overhaul and LASIK to get rid of her glasses, Patricia is ready for a pop quiz in Beauty 101 from the Glam Squad. Now Patricia can spot the slackers in the back of her classroom, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: First Class Male
programme.desc: Daryl is a postal worker who commutes nearly 2 hours each way to work. This hard working father doesn't have time to get haircuts, shave or shop for clothes. Now its time for Daryl to take care of himself.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Serving Up a New Look
programme.desc: Dirk has been a busy restaurant owner for as long as he can remember. Long hours running three different establishments kept him from ever having time to take care of himself. Now, he's retired and ready to get on with life, but can't seem to get a date.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back to Hog Heaven
programme.desc: Once comfortable on the back of her husband's Harley, this biker babe has lost all confidence in her looks. Now her aging appearance is keeping her from the fun things in life – all that used to make her happy.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Shopping For a New Look
programme.desc: Karyn is a busy working wife and mother of three, whose current frumpy appearance isn't matching the way she feels inside. It's the goal of our experts to fashion Karyn a more youthful, trendsetting look as we try make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringing Out The Spunk
programme.desc: Cat has a dream job working with rock stars and she lost 125 pounds with diet and exercise. She's worked hard to get where she is, but its left her looking more 30-something than 20-something. Our team is ready to jam on her makeover and do what it takes.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!
programme.desc: Dorothy is a single mother of two whose life changed recently when her long time employer closed its doors. Dorothy knows that years of smoking and the stress of raising her sons alone has aged her.
programme.sub-title: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Make Under
programme.desc: Hair stylist Dawn has a big personality that's hidden her perpetual weight problem. She needs to slim down her appearance. With help, Dawn sheds pounds and years off of her appearance.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are enjoying being together but agree to keep their relationship under wraps for the moment. However, they're unaware Georgina has heard their every word!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: Danny and Alice's project to re-habilitate a group of circus elephants has been a huge success but now they have too many elephants on Leopard's Den, so they urgently need to move the circus herd to the National Park.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is helping to build a new school in the township but when Danny hurts his back he begins to have a crisis about his age. Danny and Alice are surprised when Vanessa comes to them for advice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Mara is hosting a beauty pageant and Rowan realises he needs all the publicity he can get. He buys a tiger from a zoo and convinces Alice he plans to rehabilitate it. Alice is enjoying working with her brother and even defends him to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Alice have been preparing a cheetah for release in the wild but for some reason Danny's mind isn't on the job. He's been pre-occupied because he plans to buy a ring and propose to Alice!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are taking a well deserved holiday but Olivia's upset to learn they're leaving that day. Angry at missing out on a driving lesson, she decides to take the jeep out on her own.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Alice is enjoying her new job at Mara even though her animal census has revealed they have a lone male hyena that needs a pack. Du Plessis isn't happy about Alice working for next door.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Danny's continued estrangement from Alice is really starting to take its toll. Over at Mara, Alice puts on a brave face as she meets Tom Cox, the owner of a rare male black leopard.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: The embassy visits a convicted drug dealer in the world's most notorious prison. But Steven claims he's the innocent victim of an undercover drug sting gone wrong.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Young Rhys calls the embassy after his businessman father is arrested and jailed for fraud. Can Rhys raise the bail money to get him out of jail? It's a race against the clock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Ash contacts the embassy convinced he's going to die after days of partying. The notorious Thai bucket strikes again! The embassy needs to uncover the truth. Is he really in danger or is he suffering from alcohol poisoning?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: On Tour: Air Show
programme.desc: At this year's airfield festival, daredevil pilots assemble in their rare aircraft to show everything that can be conjured up in the sky. We meet a lot of aerobatic experts and their amazing flying machines here.

programme.title: On Tour: Dubai Motor Show
programme.desc: Every two years the Dubai Motor Show gets bigger and bigger, this 11th edition is expecting more than 100.000 visitors for the first time. Over 500 cars are on display, so how to draw the attention?

programme.title: On Tour: XCC Finale Triptis
programme.desc: A season final of superlatives - The XCC. Italy, Czech Republic, Austria and Germany send their best Enduro and Motocross riders to the toughest battle for the coveted title: European Cross Country Champion.

programme.title: On Tour: Snow Mobiles
programme.desc: At the grand Winter-opening of the Alps, no expense or effort is spared to turn the Austrian town into a snow-covered track for the 5th time. Professionals and celebrities provide a snow battle like no other.

programme.title: On Tour: Yeti Trophy
programme.desc: The Yeti Trophy. An iconic winter race for quads, ATVs and side-by-side vehicles. 200 drivers of the hardiest of varieties start in an extraordinary exciting hunt. The dirtier, muddier and more difficult, the better!

programme.title: On Tour: Boat Show Duesseldorf
programme.desc: Experience elegance, is the motto at the super yachts at the Dusseldorf Boat Show!

programme.title: On Tour: Kings of Xtreme
programme.desc: On Tour today at the 'Kings of Xtreme' in Leipzig. And 'Kings of Xtreme' definitely means one thing: extreme! Freestyle motocross, not only on usual motocross bikes, but also on BMX-bikes, quads and a snowmobile.

programme.title: On Tour: Snow & Ice Drifting
programme.desc: Austria, at the lake Zenz, a very cool event is taking place: The snow and ice drifting, and of course here our presenter will be learning how to drift today. And he does it with the coolest rally drivers of the scene - Team Orange.

programme.title: On Tour: Steinbeisser Trophy
programme.desc: Steinbeißer Trophy is a must for every offroad fan. Machine versus nature - that's the motto of this trophy. It gets tough when the drivers compete against each other in their up to 800 hp monsters.

programme.title: On Tour: Monster Truck Stunts
programme.desc: Today we visit the Bosslé Helldrivers and they do a gnarly stuntshow for the past forty years and I am part of it. Frightened to death but bravely part of the stunt show.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Bella Italia
programme.desc: Today in Perfect Ride: on the road in Bella Italia - the country well known for 'la dolce vita', Lamborghini, Ferrari and Mille Miglia.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Extreme Tuning
programme.desc: Chip tuning, pedal box - how useful are they? Patrick Simon is on the lookout for extra horsepower in Norway. BMW 1 Series, Viper or Ferrari? Which one is better? The ultimate coolness check.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Crazy Rides
programme.desc: The car world just gets crazier and crazier! From three-wheeled retro cars such as the Reliant Rialto, which tended to tip over at every bend? And freaky bikes with maximum speed of up to 150mph!

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Moment of Force
programme.desc: Today's Perfect Ride episode is all about power and torque: Perfect, faster, further - racer Dennis Rostek drives it to the top. With Mathilda Racing on the Nurburgring Nordschleife.
